text: With my nephew Kaedan today in Historic Tombstone! He showed his respect for Les Moore at Boot Hill and took photos with the Earp and Doc Holliday actors after the live reenactment. Great outdoor activity as we all continue to fight the pandemic, while showing support for our unique history in Cochise County and in Arizona!

text: Shae and I were able to spend some time with my nephew Kaedan this week. After some yard work, we went to the Reid Park Zoo, (which is a place I used to take his father). He particularly liked the jaguar. The Zoo is a community treasure!

text: Was thrilled to be able to watch some of the Heritage Flight Training at Davis Monthan Air Force Base from my home back patio (first photo below just above my citrus trees) this morning. It recalled to mind last year's event (other photos) where I was thrilled to be able to bring my nephew to the base to see the training. I'm glad to see he's interested in fighter aircraft!
